      "solution": "#include <stdlib.h>\n#include <stdio.h>\n#include <string.h>\n#include <inttypes.h>\n\n#define MAX(a,b) ( ( (a)>(b) ) ? (a):(b) )\n\n/**\n * let's build two incremental function\n * pn: the maximum amount he can make if he robs house n, considering houses [0..n]\n * qn: the maximum amount he can make if he does not rob house n, considering houses [0..n]\n * the computation is:\n * qn = maximum (qn-1, pn-1) // as we don't take house n, we keep best result\n * pn = qn-1 + house[n] // we take n, we cannot have taken n-1\n * \n * Improvement options\n *  - enumerate the chosen houses\n *  - try the same game on a 2D map\n **/\nint main()\n{\n    int N;\n    int64_t in[100];\n    scanf(\"%d\", &N);\n\n    scanf(\"%\" SCNd64, &in[0]);\n    // The maximum amount Rob can take if he visits house n\n    int64_t pn=in[0];\n    // The maximum amount Rob can take if he does not visit house n\n    int64_t qn=0;\n\n\n    for (int i = 1; i < N; i++) {\n        int64_t pn1 = pn;\n        int64_t qn1 = qn;\n        scanf(\"%\" SCNd64, &in[i]);\n        pn=qn1+in[i];       // pn is qn (as house n-1 was not visited) + value of house n\n        qn=MAX(pn1,qn1);    // qn is the max of the n-1 possibilities\n    }\n    printf(\"%\" PRId64 \"\\n\",MAX(pn,qn));\n    return 0;\n}",
      "statement": "Rob is a robber. He wants to operate a last time in the neighborhood before he leaves.\nHe has been informed about the values of the content of each house of a street but he is careful and when he robs in a house he avoids the 2 houses aside (left and right).\nWhat is the maximum money he can make without being caught?\n! Be warned ! Some houses have been trapped. They have been rated with negative values.\n\nFor example, for a street of 3 houses with values: (A: 1) - (B: 2) - (C: 3), Rob shall visit houses A and C (he takes 4).\nIn this other street: (A: 1) - (B: 15) - (C: 10) - (D: 13) - (E: 16), Rob should avoid C and D and visit only B and E (he takes 31).",
